She was 76. Gerber gave up her acting career in 1966 to be with two-time Oscar-nominated screenwriter Terry Southern (Easy Rider, Dr. Strangelove, The Cincinnati Kid). item.title: Can I use poly pipe for sprinkler system?
item.description: Answer 200 PSI is the maximum pressure that the typical 1″ PVC pipe used for lawn sprinkler systems is rated to endure. Poly pipe of comparable size (1″) is rated to resist 100 PSI. In fact, for polyethylene to attain the same pressure rating as PVC, the walls would need to be twice as thick as those of PVC. Squeeze clamps or saddle fittings are used with poly pipe, and they are not rated.

item.title: Can L.A.'s Frogtown Survive Gentrification?
item.description: There’s a bend along the Los Angeles River in Elysian Valley’s Frogtown where you can see the Hollywood sign lording over the city, but Frogtown feels light years away from the glitz of LA. The low key neighborhood, which runs parallel to a soft bottom portion of the LA River a few miles east of Hollywood, is a strange combination of residential living and converted industrial warehouse space. Egrets and blue herons hover around the water near trees that sprout through the river’s concrete flood channels, a reminder that the natural world always has the upper hand.

item.description: Distance: approx 365 miles Drive time: 5.5 hours (non-stop)  Ask anyone over the age of 45 about their bucket list and driving Route 66 will likely be in the top three. Named the “Mother Road” by John Steinbeck, the original route crossed eight states and three time zones and though most of the original road was decommissioned by 1984, there are still sections which make popular road trips. The 400-mile stretch between St Louis, Missouri and Amarillo, Texas starts from downtown St Louis, winds through Joplin, Cuba and Oklahoma and is dotted with historic motels, diners and kitsch roadside attractions like the 80ft-long Blue Whale of Catoosa.
